<dl id="n36193a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36193a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36193a"> 193(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mottoes on wall</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">As to the gentlemen, each of them tranquilly smoked his pipe, and seemed lost in contemplation of the blue and <mark>white tiles</mark> with which the fireplaces were decorated; <mark>wherein sundry passages of Scripture were piously portrayed</mark>. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 100</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
